      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a really strong angle for the drama. the tension over the food is a cool touch. i was thinking about the socioeconomic side of it to make it feel more grounded. in a family like this, would the struggle or the neighborhood they live in usually be a big topic of conversation during these dinners, or is it more about them just trying to keep up appearances? basically, does the environment usually dictate the mood of the meal?",
